<br>
By the time we get to Plane of Time, there will be nothing really exciting left to loot. Another thing, it is easy for someone to get ft15 without even buying the POP expansion. <br>
<br>
As far as risk vs reward goes, how much difference in power is there going to be between a POP equipped caster and a VT equipped caster that never bought the expansion? Yes, there's 9% in focus damage, but it's not a consistant 9%, it's random. How many people <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>really</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> notice a difference in power between a 30% POP focus item and a 26% VT focus item? I refuse to believe a 35% wrath item in plane of time is the end all in player power.<br>
<br>
With an Elemental planes equipped tank, I run oom tons in exp groups chain casting still, even with full buffs and 200+AA's. <br>
<br>
Yes running oom is rare in POP for some, but some of us would like to know that there's a difference in power when the need arises, and mana regen is the best way to increase power. Yes, a large mana pool will give you a couple of extra nukes over the VT guy, but when you're oom, you both are back to square one, equals with 15ft.<br>
