<br>
 All worn ATK and Primal/Prismatic proc'd avatar counts towards the 250 worn ATK cap. There's 2 avatar's in the game.<br>
 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2434&amp;source=Live">Proc Avatar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
 <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1598&amp;source=Live">Shaman Avatar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Shaman cast avatars do not in any way count towards the cap, just like mana regen buffs(clarity line anyone?) do not count towards the FT cap.<br>
<br>
 I believe rangers found direct atk increases to be about 10atk = 1% dmg. So if you're at the 250 cap that's 12.5% more damage. Though atk buffs actually give 1.33x their listed value. So 332atk actually. So 16.6%.<br>
<br>
